text: hey guys, had a good chat with Andy
He's going to remain in the loop so we don't lose sight of the project goals, which will help us keep focused on ours.

I posted today's build on BaseCamp, I'd like them to try it out. All pictures in /Pictures/SeeSay should now be shown, regardless of captions (it might look junky if they have pictures left over from previous versions of the app), and I updated the UI to be a bit closer to their slideshow, with the current app functionality. The keywords "google", "search", "what is this/that" trigger a Goggles search, and "video", "youtube", "watch" should take you to the self-cleaning toilet video in the youtube app.
And if you don't trigger one of the special keywords, you still have a captioned photo that you can share or delete.
